Description: RPG II to LLVM compiler and static analyzer
 rpgc compiles DOS/VS RPG II source into native Linux executables using
 LLVM 19 as its backend. It covers the RPG II program cycle (file I/O,
 control levels, subroutines), O-spec output with edit codes, the full
 arithmetic set, arrays, indicators, and -O0..-O3 optimization. Generated
 programs link against a small C runtime, librpgruntime.a, installed
 alongside rpgc.
 .
 This package also installs rpg-analyze, a static-analysis CLI for RPG II
 source that reuses the compiler's frontend but does not link LLVM.
